asked the Minister of Health (1) whether he is aware that Mr. J. McCormack, a transferred war worker from Glasgow to Luton, is occu-


pying requisitioned property at 24, Chapel Street, for which he is paying 31s. per week rent and 22s. per week rates; and whether he proposes to take any action with a view to lowering these charges;

(2) who are the owners of the requisitioned property at 24, Chapel Street, Luton; and what compensation they are receiving by way of rent from the Luton Town Council.
